Name: pseudomembranous conjunctivitis
Definition: A acute conjunctivitis which involves a fibrin-rich exudate formation on the surface of the conjunctiva. Infectious causes of pseudomembranes include Corynebacterium diphtheriae

Name: serous conjunctivitis except viral
Definition: A viral acute conjunctivitis that is characterized by conjunctival inflammation and serous discharge.

Name: acute contagious conjunctivitis
Definition: A bacterial acute conjunctivitis that is characterized by highly contagious conjunctival hypermia and mucopurulent discharge and has_material basis in Hemophilius Aegypticus.

Name: obsolete premature rupture of the fetal membranes
Definition: A bacterial acute conjunctivitis that is characterized by highly contagious conjunctival hypermia and mucopurulent discharge and has_material basis in Hemophilius Aegypticus.

Name: conjunctival folliculosis
Definition: An acute conjunctivitis characterized by conjunctival folliculosis and follicular hypertrophy of the palpebral conjunctivae.

Name: obsolete spinal enthesopathy
Definition: An acute conjunctivitis characterized by conjunctival folliculosis and follicular hypertrophy of the palpebral conjunctivae.
